<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-04T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-04T07:00:00-05:00" n="641" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d641">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/139</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WHR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-04T13:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 6, 2.03
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2768. I considered it highly advantageous and urgent in view of my
                                2765 that the information contained in your 1554 be imparted to the
                                President of the Republic; therefore, acting on discretion allowed
                                me, I imparted to him unofficially on the 3d instant certain
                                portions this telegram. He desired me to assure you that he was
                                touched and thoroughly recognized America’s noble attitude in this
                                matter.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WHR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>